<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-06-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-06-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="299" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Norwegian Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-06-07"><hi rend="italic">June 7,
                                1906</hi></date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that Maj.
                            William W. Gibson, U. S. Army, has been directed to attend Mr. Charles
                            H. Graves, ambassador extraordinary, on special mission to represent the
                            United States at the coronation of King Haakon of Norway, as military
                            assistant, and that Lieut. Commander John H. Gibbons, U. S. Navy, has
                            been selected for the same service as naval assistant.</p>
                        <p>I beg that you will do me the favor to notify your Government of these
                            selections.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>